      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Returns true iff this cons list is equal to the object o.

        This cons list is equal to o iff o is a cons list of the same length as this cons list, and the elements of this cons list and o are pairwise equal (using equals(Object)).

        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Parameters:
        o - the object to test for equality with this cons list
        Returns:
        true iff o is a cons list with identical elements to this cons list

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Returns the hash code of this cons list.

        Note that this method traverses the entire list, and its time complexity is therefore O(n) with respect to the number of elements in the list.
